Subcapitulum (
Fig. 22
). All 4 pairs of paralabial setae present in adults:
pl 1
small, conical; With's organ (
pl 2
) membranous, discoid; rutella (
pl 3
) with 1 row of 5 teeth, inserted dorso-laterally;
pl 4
very small, inserted dorsal on subcapitulum. In addition, 4 circumbuccal ( cb ), and 6–10 median and subcapitular ( vm (in part), lvm , ldm , vp , lvp ) setae. Sexual dimorphism indistinct. Lateral lips with distinct canals. Larva with only 2 circumbuccal setae, With's organ reduced to a membranous cone, and rutella reduced to large lobes without distinct teeth. Larva, proto-, deuto-, and tritonymphs with, respectively, 0, 2 , 2–3 , and 5–6 median and subcapitular setae.
